OL,3,CThousands of children wait years for
OL,4,Cautism support
OL,6,FOne parent, seeking an assessment for
OL,7,Fher child, told the report's authors,
OL,8,Ftrying to receive an assessment was
OL,9,F"an absolute nightmare ... our systems
OL,10,Fin health and our systems in education
OL,11,Fdon't link and can't talk, and we
OL,12,Fcan't transfer things over, and things
OL,13,Fhad to be logged in one place and not
OL,14,Fanother."
OL,16,FThe authors argue children and young
OL,17,Fpeople with autism and conditions such
OL,18,Fas ADHD can thrive in mainstream
OL,19,Feducation if their needs are supported
OL,20,Fin a timely way.
