OL,3,CThousands of children wait years for
OL,4,Cautism support
OL,6,FWith waiting times increasing, there
OL,7,Fis a growing risk to education
OL,8,Foutcomes, with evidence suggesting
OL,9,Fthat many autistic children are ending
OL,10,Fup in expensive Alternative Provision.
OL,11,FThe report also describes how a major
OL,12,Fbarrier to existing systems is the
OL,13,Fperceived need for a medical diagnosis
OL,14,Fof autism before any child can receive
OL,15,Fsupport, with the perception among
OL,16,Fschools that this is a requirement,
OL,17,Fpreventing some children from
OL,18,Faccessing support.
