OL,3,CThousands of children wait years for
OL,4,Cautism support
OL,6,F"Autistic children with a referral who
OL,7,Fare waiting for an assessment are at
OL,8,Fsignificantly greater risk of
OL,9,Fexclusion from school, with all the
OL,10,Ffurther risks that can bring. If
OL,11,Fwaiting times continue to increase, so
OL,12,Fcan the risk of increased exclusion
OL,13,Fand poorer educational outcomes for
OL,14,Fautistic children.
OL,16,F"The evidence shows the need to move
OL,17,Fto a system of support that responds
OL,18,Fto the needs of autistic children,
OL,19,Frather than waiting for diagnosis
OL,20,Fbefore any help appears.
